TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hart, Oliver
AU  - Holmstrom, Bengt
T1  - A Theory of Firm Scope*
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/05/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2010.125.2.483
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 125
IS  - 2
SP  - 483
EP  - 513
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The formal literature on firm boundaries has assumed that ex post conflicts are resolved through bargaining. In reality, parties often simply exercise their decision rights. We develop a model, based on shading, in which the use of authority has a central role. We consider two firms deciding whether to adopt a common standard. Nonintegrated firms may fail to coordinate if one firm loses. An integrated firm can internalize the externality, but puts insufficient weight on employee benefits. We use our approach to understand why Cisco acquired StrataCom, a provider of new transmission technology. We also analyze delegation.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2010.125.2.483
ER  - 



