TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bohnet, Iris
AU  - Herrmann, Benedikt
AU  - Zeckhauser, Richard
T1  - Trust and the Reference Points for Trustworthiness in Gulf and Western Countries*
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/05/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2010.125.2.811
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 125
IS  - 2
SP  - 811
EP  - 828
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Why is private investment so low in Gulf compared to Western countries? We investigate cross-regional differences in trust and reference points for trustworthiness as possible factors. Experiments controlling for cross-regional differences in institutions and beliefs about trustworthiness reveal that Gulf citizens pay much more than Westerners to avoid trusting, and hardly respond when returns to trusting change. These differences can be explained by subjects' gain/loss utility relative to their region's reference point for trustworthiness. The relation-based production of trust in the Gulf induces higher levels of trustworthiness, albeit within groups, than the rule-based interactions prevalent in the West.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2010.125.2.811
ER  - 



